
# Google Maps API Key Setup Guide
# Before proceeding, there are some important things to know:
# 1. Do not write your actual API key into this file.
# 2. Do not commit your actual API key to GitHub.
# 3. Each developer must create a dedicated API key.
#
# Now begin setting up the API:
# First, create a dedicated Google Maps API key
# 1. Visit: https://console.cloud.google.com/
# 2. Create a new project, locate ‘APIs & Services’, then click ‘Libraries’
# 3. Enable the following APIs:
#      • Maps JavaScript API
#      • Places API
#      • Places API (New)
# 4. Then navigate to APIs & Services and go to Credentials
# 5. Click “Create credentials”, then locate “API keys”
#
# After obtaining the API key, perform the following steps:
# 1. Create a file named .env.local in the project root directory
# Add the following content to the file, replacing YOUR_API_KEY_HERE:
#
#  VITE_GOOGLE_MAPS_API_KEY=your_google_maps_api_key
#  VITE_API_BASE_URL=http://localhost:8080
#
#
#
# 2. Ensure .env.local is included in .gitignore
# This prevents the API key from being pushed to GitHub.
# No one should commit this file.
